    <text id="B1233T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Tukey writes a letter recommending William Dews and attesting to his character.
                    Tukey and Dews worked together in Staunton while Tukey was Agent there.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">RF &amp;
                        AL</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Head Quarters">Hd Qrs</abbr> 2nd <abbr
                            expan="Division">Div</abbr> 6th Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brigadier General">Brig Genl</abbr> O.
                            Brown<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant">Asst</abbr> Commissioner<lb/>Richmond,
                            <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-07-17">July 17th 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Bowling Green</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="General">Gen'l</abbr>
                    </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>This will introduce to your favorable notice Mr. Wm J Dews of Richmond Va. A man
                    tried and true in the Union Cause who is seeking a position in the Bureau as
                    Agent or Clerk.</p>

                <p>I have had a three years acquaintance with him and it affords me great pleasure
                    to <orig reg="recommend">reccomend</orig> him as a Man of Excellent character
                    and business attainments.</p>

                <p>Any favors you can show him will be worthily bestowed.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very <abbr expan="Respectfully">Respt'y</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>FS Tukey</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
